Reports that the US National Security Agency was spying on Brazilian oil company Petrobras and gaining access to data held by US cloud service providers, including Google and Yahoo, have raised corporate paranoia caused by government surveillance to new heights.
The last straw was the news that Chancellor Angela Merkel&#39;s phone had been tapped for perhaps a decade.
If Europe&#39;s most powerful person can be targeted, then of course business leaders are also potential targets.
Snowden made clear the intense collaboration between US intelligence agencies and companies.
I think it&#39;s likely that this data is being used for mutual benefit.
“Germany needs to wake up,” says Oliver Grün, president of BITMi, which represents German small and medium-sized IT companies.
