The Americans are spying on us on a commercial and industrial level, and we are spying on them too, because it is in our national interest to protect our businesses.
Corporate leaders usually don&#39;t like to brag about the countermeasures they have taken, as this can give an advantage to the adversary.
Large companies have long adopted the idea that taking a free flash drive at a trade show or leaving a laptop unattended in a hotel room is imprudent to say the least.
Ulrich Hackenberg, a board member at automaker Audi, says it&#39;s been standard practice for years to collect mobile phones before board meetings so they can&#39;t be used as listening devices.
